{
  "stem": "16106.2",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There were very few Latvians, some, who would have helped us to hide or not-- not reported us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It wasn't-- it was not happening in Libau too much-- very little.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Here and there, one, not what happened in other countries-- it was-- they were extremely happy to cooperate with the-- it was so bad that they wrote-- the German army, the head of the German army wrote a letter to Berlin and asked them to stop the senseless killings, the tortures of the Jews, which is not acceptable for them, and that the-- the German army gets demoralized by whatever's happening to the mass-- mass killings and the-- this whole bloodshed.",
      "word_count": 81
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "That was in July.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we had-- we could only shop in the Jewish store, of course.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we got Jewish-- for Jewish allotments.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in the they usually were writing what we-- what we will get next week or what have you, yeah?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we could-- more or less, we were-- everybody-- I mean, if we wouldn't have been shot, we would have managed.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You would sell one's-- one's plates, or sell one's jewelry, and get for that.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then, there was a German lady, Fraulein-- there was a German lady who worked for our-- for the-- our neighbors [NON-ENGLISH] person.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She was-- she loved him very much, Mr.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Edelstein.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And she was his secretary for many, many years.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And she came after curfew.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And she went to all the Jews she knew, especially to us, whom she knew personally, and she brought us delicacies, which she cooked, yeah, and cookies, and marinated mushrooms.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I remember that very well.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, I do, but not right now.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH] And she-- and she took all our jewelry--",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Fraulein-- oh, but--",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
